page.title: 01Garvald Birds
page.content: Owing to the varies terain in the area there are many different species to be found. The usual garden birds:robins, sparrows, blackbirds, chaffinches, dunnocks & 3 kinds of tits being in the majority. The burn running through the area brings herons, dippers, mallard duck, moorhens & wagtails. In the woods are to be found pigeons, collared doves, tree creepers, tawny owls, woodcock and the occasional green woodpecker. In one wood there is a rookery & the rooks are joined by jackdaws & gulls following the plough. The arable land encourages pheasants, partridges & the occasional grouse from the nearby moors. The summer visitors include swallows, house and sand martins, willow warblers and chiffchaffs. Autumn brings fieldfares, redwings and bramblings.
